Enabling Auto-login Linux Lite
Two methods to choose from:

1. Open a terminal, type in the following:

Code:
gksu lxdm-config
Place a tick in Automatic Login

Next time you reboot you will auto-login.

2. Open a terminal, type in the following:

Code:
sudo leafpad /etc/lxdm/lxdm.conf

At line 3 remove the # from the start of the line, put your login name after the = sign and save the file. Next time you reboot, you will automatically login.
